Still the questions remain:

00:47.380 --> 00:52.260
Was it economic,
was it social, or was it cultural?

00:52.427 --> 00:55.430
Or was it simply a matter of human nature?

00:55.597 --> 01:00.185
Why did some people do something
and others nothing at all?

01:00.644 --> 01:03.105
Good job, Mr. Bowden.

01:03.313 --> 01:07.818
It's nice to see a few more A's this time around.
Including Mr. Bowden's, of course.

01:12.864 --> 01:18.829
This concludes
our week on the Holocaust.

01:21.581 --> 01:28.380
If you want to know more, the
library is an excellent resource.

05:37.546 --> 05:40.340
Becky Trask likes you.

05:43.552 --> 05:47.305
- You know who I'm talking about?
- I know who she is.

05:47.472 --> 05:52.936
- I'll think about it.
- No, just do it.

05:53.103 --> 05:59.025
- Could you give me your trig notes?
- I knew you'd want something.

05:59.234 --> 06:03.572
- I'll bring them in tomorrow.
- Ask Becky out.

06:03.738 --> 06:07.325
- What are you doing after school?
- I'm busy.

07:44.297 --> 07:47.801
All right, I'm coming.

07:49.344 --> 07:52.264
For God's sake.

07:57.769 --> 08:01.022
Yes?

08:03.233 --> 08:06.653
What do you want?

08:08.071 --> 08:13.285
- Are you selling something?
- I have your newspaper.

08:17.247 --> 08:22.043
- I'm not selling anything.
- Then what do you want?

08:22.252 --> 08:27.299
- I just want to talk.
- Talk?

08:28.049 --> 08:31.470
I don't have anything
to say to you. Good day.

08:31.636 --> 08:35.932
Bergen-Belsen, January '43-June '43.

08:36.099 --> 08:39.852
Auschwitz, June '43-June '44.

08:40.061 --> 08:45.192
Then you went to Patin.
After that, you disappeared.

08:45.358 --> 08:50.238
But in 1 965
you were spotted in West Berlin.

08:50.447 --> 08:56.870
Listen, boy,
I don't have time for this game.

08:57.079 --> 09:01.249
- Leave before I call the police.
- Call them.

09:01.458 --> 09:05.754
I'm sure they'd love to meet you.

09:06.963 --> 09:13.053
- Who are you?
- My name is Todd Bowden.

09:13.220 --> 09:18.183
I really want to talk to you.
Could you let me in for a minute?

09:18.391 --> 09:22.312
Please, Mr. Dussander.

09:26.108 --> 09:30.278
All of this because you saw
an old man in a raincoat?

09:30.445 --> 09:34.616
It wasn't that easy.
These pictures are 40 years old.

09:34.825 --> 09:37.786
But they looked like those I took.

09:37.994 --> 09:44.334
- You took photographs of me?
- Yeah, but even then I wasn't sure.

09:44.501 --> 09:48.964
I needed real proof. So I dusted
your mail box for fingerprints.

09:49.881 --> 09:55.971
That's harder than people think.
You need a lot of stuff.

09:56.179 --> 10:01.768
- You were at the movies.
- You dusted my mail box.

10:01.935 --> 10:05.772
You took photographs of me.
What else did you do?

10:05.981 --> 10:10.485
I had a copy of your fingerprints
from your lsraeli wanted sheet.

10:10.652 --> 10:14.072
It's all on database
at the university.

10:16.741 --> 10:20.328
Are you okay?

10:21.538 --> 10:27.002
- Would you care for a drink?
- How about milk?

10:36.344 --> 10:42.517
- Have you told your parents?
- Do you think I'm crazy?

10:43.393 --> 10:48.690
It takes eight "compares"
to get a print accepted in court.

10:48.857 --> 10:53.361
One or two is not hard to find,
but eight, that's really tough.

10:53.528 --> 11:00.827
It all sounds very exciting, but
all your work has been for nothing.

11:00.994 --> 11:04.372
I found 14 compares.

11:07.751 --> 11:14.633
Boy, what you have done ...
I have to explain this to you.

11:14.800 --> 11:19.930
- What you have done is a violation.
- Like decompression experiments?

11:20.097 --> 11:25.519
- That's a violation.
- I'm calling the police.

11:25.685 --> 11:29.439
Your father's going
to beat your behind.

11:29.606 --> 11:34.736
- He doesn't believe in violence.
- They should start.

11:44.204 --> 11:47.874
My name is Denker.

11:50.335 --> 11:53.547
Arthur Denker.

11:55.006 --> 12:01.096
I'm an American.
I became a citizen in 1955.

12:04.891 --> 12:08.228
I vote.

12:09.521 --> 12:16.111
You've no right to come here
and say these lies about me.

12:17.654 --> 12:23.326
I have your fingerprints.
I have your photographs.

12:23.493 --> 12:28.623
One way or another,
I'll get them to the right people.

12:33.587 --> 12:37.799
This is unbelievable.

12:41.428 --> 12:44.848
What do you want? Tell me.

12:47.017 --> 12:50.687
- I want to hear about it.
- Hear about what?

12:50.854 --> 12:54.775
The stories. Everything.

12:55.817 --> 12:58.570
What everything?

12:58.737 --> 13:03.033
Everything they're afraid
to show us in school.

13:03.200 --> 13:06.953
You were there.
You did those things.

13:07.204 --> 13:12.334
No one can tell it better than you.
That's all I want.

13:12.542 --> 13:18.006
Then I'll leave you alone.
And just so you know ...

13:20.383 --> 13:23.136
Everything that I have on you, -

13:23.303 --> 13:27.432
- the compares, the wanted sheet,
all the photographs, -

13:27.599 --> 13:33.063
- are in a safe place. If anything
happens to me, they'll be found.

13:36.441 --> 13:41.238
Why should I consider doing this?

13:41.947 --> 13:46.410
Because you hung up the phone.

14:07.848 --> 14:11.268
Judging by the results
of your first exam, -

14:11.435 --> 14:15.981
- for most of you, we moved
too fast through chapter one.

14:17.149 --> 14:23.238
How many of you
think you know what sociology is?

14:26.825 --> 14:32.622
As I thought.
All right, turn to chapter two.

14:39.963 --> 14:44.217
Once they were in the chamber,
how long did it take? A minute?

14:45.260 --> 14:50.056
No, the Prussic acid
took about 15 minutes.

14:50.265 --> 14:55.979
But the monoxide could take
an hour, sometimes more.

14:56.730 --> 15:01.610
What happened to them ... exactly?

15:04.446 --> 15:09.493
It was a mess. They would
lose control of their bodies.

15:09.701 --> 15:15.040
They vomited, urinated
and defecated themselves.

15:15.207 --> 15:19.628
Even though the gas
came through vents in the ceiling, -

15:19.836 --> 15:22.464
- they climbed up on each other, -

15:22.672 --> 15:27.636
- desperately reaching for fresh air
that wasn't there.

15:27.803 --> 15:34.810
- There was a mountain of bodies.
- What about the children?

15:36.603 --> 15:40.440
On the bottom.

15:41.691 --> 15:47.489
Did anyone ever survive it?

15:49.533 --> 15:56.832
One time, the gas didn't work.

15:56.998 --> 16:03.338
There was a leak in the pipes,
so oxygen mixed with the monoxide.

16:04.256 --> 16:10.178
It was horrible. After an hour,
they were still moving.

16:10.720 --> 16:16.810
Stumbling around the room
like drunks, their eyes glassy.

16:17.602 --> 16:20.313
What did you do?

16:20.480 --> 16:24.651
I ordered more gas,
but we didn't know about the leak.

16:24.818 --> 16:30.449
Soon they began to twitch all over,
like they were dancing.

16:30.615 --> 16:37.539
Some fell to their knees,
laughing in a high-pitched scream.

16:38.457 --> 16:42.586
Even the guards were frightened.

16:44.921 --> 16:51.803
They didn't die. After two hours,
I sent five men in with rifles.

16:57.225 --> 17:01.438
It's getting dark.
Your mother will be worried.

17:01.605 --> 17:06.734
Shit! I've got to go. Tomorrow,
I want to hear the end of this.

17:06.902 --> 17:10.155
The end?

17:12.907 --> 17:16.411
The end.

18:12.592 --> 18:17.347
Todd, are you up?
Let's go. Joey's outside.

18:17.514 --> 18:23.937
- Tell him I'm coming.
- I woke you half an hour ago.

18:24.813 --> 18:29.067
- Todd?
- I must have fallen asleep.

18:29.234 --> 18:34.781
I'm going to see a client tonight.
There's some chicken in the fridge.

18:34.948 --> 18:41.538
- I'm eating at Mr. Denker's house.
- And do what, watch TV?

18:41.705 --> 18:46.752
I read books to him.
Don't worry about it.

18:46.960 --> 18:54.176
Invite him over here.
Daddy and I still want to meet him.

18:54.342 --> 18:56.636
The policeman said:

18:56.845 --> 19:01.975
"Mr. Denker, if you can't see
the road, you shouldn't be driving.

19:02.184 --> 19:05.020
"How many fingers am I holding up?

19:05.187 --> 19:09.649
I said,
"Well now, officer, let me guess."

19:10.442 --> 19:13.612
"One?"

19:15.489 --> 19:20.452
That was the end of my driving
in America. I take the bus.

19:21.161 --> 19:27.918
I'm now in a wheelchair, but
my sight is not what it used to be.

19:30.253 --> 19:34.091
That's a white-tailed buck.

19:34.299 --> 19:40.555
- We used to live in Carolina.
- Dick shot that seven years ago.

19:40.722 --> 19:45.393
Your grandson never told me
he came from a family of hunters.

19:45.602 --> 19:50.357
- Todd never took a shine to guns.
- No, he's good at other things.

19:50.524 --> 19:55.570
- Baseball is Todd's game.
- Arthur, you want a cigar?

19:55.779 --> 20:00.659
I'll have one of my cigarettes.
Where are they?

20:00.826 --> 20:04.496
Let me help you with that.

20:04.663 --> 20:11.753
Your generosity humbles me.
Thank you for an enchanting evening.

20:16.133 --> 20:21.805
Arthur, can I ask you
a personal question?

20:22.681 --> 20:26.435
What did you do during the war?

20:30.313 --> 20:34.317
I was in the reserves,
as were most young men, Victor.

20:34.484 --> 20:38.697
My poor eyesight
kept me out of combat, thank God.

20:38.864 --> 20:45.996
I spent most of the war
washing hospital linen.

20:50.500 --> 20:53.253
You're quiet tonight.

20:53.420 --> 20:57.340
I'm sorry, it's just that
I've heard all these stories before.

20:57.549 --> 21:03.138
- Todd!
- The boy's just being honest.

21:04.681 --> 21:09.478
That's a privilege that men
must sometimes give up.

21:12.063 --> 21:15.484
That reminds me ...

21:15.650 --> 21:23.075
It must have been my first year
at the university ...

21:23.241 --> 21:28.455
My men took turns shooting them,
but there were so many.

21:28.622 --> 21:35.670
Three bodies were packed into each
oven. They were ground into ash.

21:35.837 --> 21:41.176
A whole town was
wiped off the face of the earth.

21:53.730 --> 21:58.693
Still it wasn't enough for Himmler.
It was a dark year.

21:58.860 --> 22:03.657
He ordered every Jew in Kiev
to come to the Babi Jar ravine.

22:03.907 --> 22:08.870
Remember, the 20's
were a desperate time in Germany.

22:09.037 --> 22:13.542
The Treaty of Versailles
had left us crippled.

22:13.750 --> 22:17.587
They would hide.

22:17.754 --> 22:22.884
We always found them. If the dogs
didn't, smoke and fire would.

22:23.093 --> 22:27.389
We would round them up
and march them out to a large pit.

22:27.556 --> 22:31.393
At the time, the shooting
was no longer killing.

22:31.601 --> 22:34.896
Killing was no longer death.

22:35.105 --> 22:39.568
I will never forget
the sound that night.

22:39.734 --> 22:43.739
So many of them
on top of each another like that.

22:43.905 --> 22:49.035
After a few hours,
they began to settle.

22:52.080 --> 22:56.001
A head would fall.

22:56.209 --> 22:59.463
An arm would drop.

23:03.008 --> 23:07.888
It was a bit like the sound
of blowing leaves.

23:10.223 --> 23:13.101
What did it feel like?

23:26.531 --> 23:29.326
It had to be done.

23:29.493 --> 23:35.665
A door had been opened and
couldn't be shut. It was the end ...

23:35.832 --> 23:38.960
You don't understand.

23:40.545 --> 23:43.507
You've done it a million times.
Let's go!

24:04.444 --> 24:07.364
All right, that's it. Take a shower.

24:08.865 --> 24:12.285
- Where have you been?
- What do you mean?

24:12.536 --> 24:17.749
I tried to phone you.
There's a party on Saturday night.

24:17.958 --> 24:22.504
- I've been busy.
- Too busy for your best friend?

24:22.712 --> 24:28.969
- I've been studying a lot.
- Are you going to go?

24:29.177 --> 24:35.434
- I don't know if I can get the car.
- I know someone who'll drive you.

26:26.670 --> 26:30.173
I've been accepted!

26:30.382 --> 26:34.302
The Ritzy Vista Country Club.
My life 's ambition.

26:34.511 --> 26:41.101
Officer, can you tell me which bus
goes to the Ritzy Vista Club?

26:41.351 --> 26:44.229
Here it is.

26:44.396 --> 26:50.736
- Do you go by the country club?
- Very humorous.

27:13.383 --> 27:17.429
- Wake up.
- I'll kill you!

27:21.683 --> 27:24.603
I thought you were dead.

27:24.770 --> 27:30.942
It's Saturday. Since when do you
come here on Saturdays?

27:31.151 --> 27:35.572
I brought you something.
Aren't you going to open it?

27:36.406 --> 27:40.577
Wait.
Let me pull the shades down.

27:42.287 --> 27:45.582
- What for?
- To be safe.

27:45.749 --> 27:51.922
- The hell with this. You open it.
- Relax. Open it.

28:02.265 --> 28:06.436
You wrapped it yourself, I see.

28:21.743 --> 28:25.914
- Merry Christmas.
- Mary mother of God!

28:27.457 --> 28:32.504
- Where did you get this?
- It's pretty real.

28:37.551 --> 28:45.183
"E.F. Montgomery Costumes,
Tappan Zee, New Jersey."

28:46.435 --> 28:51.231
- Try it on.
- Have you lost your mind?

28:51.481 --> 28:55.944
- Why would I put that on?
- I thought you would like it.

28:57.404 --> 29:01.158
Like it?
You're a bigger fool than I thought.

29:01.366 --> 29:05.996
Maybe I'll put it on
and do a little shopping, right?

29:06.163 --> 29:09.499
For this indignity,
I should smash you.

29:09.666 --> 29:14.880
This is nothing compared to what
the lsraelis would do to you.

29:15.088 --> 29:20.385
Don't forget that and don't ever
forget the file I have on you.

29:20.552 --> 29:24.890
I tried to do things the nice way,
but fine, we'll do it the hard way.

29:25.056 --> 29:29.936
You'll put this on because
I want to see you in it. Move!

30:14.064 --> 30:18.527
- I see I've been promoted.
- Yeah, it's all they had.

30:18.693 --> 30:21.530
But it's a perfect fit.

30:21.822 --> 30:26.952
- It itches like hell.
- Quiet.

30:28.245 --> 30:32.791
- Put the hat on.
- Please!

30:32.958 --> 30:36.711
Please, put the hat on.

31:04.281 --> 31:07.701
Attention.

31:15.792 --> 31:19.087
What's so funny?

31:20.088 --> 31:24.009
March. Do it.

31:25.635 --> 31:29.139
I'm serious.

31:35.812 --> 31:39.816
Stop fucking around. March!

31:44.196 --> 31:47.574
That's it. March.

31:49.493 --> 31:53.246
Face right.

31:55.207 --> 31:57.584
March.

31:57.751 --> 32:01.129
Face right.

32:01.296 --> 32:04.674
March.

32:04.841 --> 32:08.970
Face right.
March.

32:13.725 --> 32:18.772
Face right. March!

32:19.022 --> 32:21.233
March!

32:32.869 --> 32:36.623
That's enough. Stop.

32:42.295 --> 32:45.882
Stop it!

33:08.947 --> 33:15.036
Boy, be careful. You play with fire.

33:25.380 --> 33:29.551
Okay,
I can tell you're not into this.

33:29.718 --> 33:34.055
No, I am. Really.
It just takes me a while.

33:34.931 --> 33:40.145
I like you. You're the only guy
who never tried to impress me.

33:43.940 --> 33:49.154
- Can I ask you something?
- Sure.

33:50.739 --> 33:55.702
Do you ever wonder
why people do the things they do?

33:55.952 --> 34:01.249
Think about it. Seriously.

34:08.799 --> 34:13.762
It's better not to think.
It's better to just do it.

34:36.159 --> 34:40.205
Who are you, kitty?

34:49.714 --> 34:54.052
It's getting cold out here, kitty.

35:11.653 --> 35:15.574
- I'm sorry.
- We can try again later.

35:15.782 --> 35:22.205
- That's never happened before.
- It's all right.

35:23.874 --> 35:28.503
Could you blow that
the other way, please.

35:31.548 --> 35:36.887
- Maybe you just don't like me.
- No, it's not that at all.

35:37.053 --> 35:42.684
- I really do.
- Maybe you just don't like girls.

36:08.460 --> 36:12.047
Kitty ...

36:12.756 --> 36:15.425
Goodbye.

36:25.227 --> 36:28.730
You motherfucker!

37:02.931 --> 37:07.894
You have five more minutes.

37:37.507 --> 37:39.634
"Dear Mr. & Mrs. Bowden."

37:39.843 --> 37:44.598
"l suggest we have a conference
about Todd's first-semester grades."

37:44.765 --> 37:48.977
"ln light of his previous
outstanding work, -

37:49.144 --> 37:54.357
- it suggests a problem which
should be addressed immediately."

37:54.524 --> 37:59.321
"Let's work out a time to meet.
Sincerely yours, Edward French."

38:00.947 --> 38:05.035
- What are you going to do?
- I'm fucked if I know.

38:05.202 --> 38:09.372
- What?
- I said, fucked if I know.

38:09.539 --> 38:16.254
- You're throwing it up hard.
- I don't need a lesson.

38:17.923 --> 38:23.136
I'm a fuck-up. My dad expects this
kind of thing from me, but you ..?

38:28.308 --> 38:34.022
- You're talking to yourself.
- I fucked up. I'll fix it.

38:35.065 --> 38:38.151
Whatever you say.

38:38.318 --> 38:43.532
What's with you and Becky?
Becky Trask, idiot.

38:44.241 --> 38:47.828
What did you call me?

38:49.621 --> 38:55.168
You're being a real dick, man.
I've got to get to practice.

39:00.048 --> 39:02.509
"Talking to yourself?"

39:03.718 --> 39:07.222
"You're being a dick."

40:30.180 --> 40:36.895
"Let's work out a time to meet."

40:37.062 --> 40:40.732
"Sincerely yours, Edward French."

40:40.982 --> 40:44.903
Who's this Edward French?
Headmaster?

40:45.695 --> 40:49.282
- Guidance counsellor.
- What is that?

40:49.491 --> 40:53.870
He guides and he counsels.
You read the letter.

40:55.872 --> 40:58.250
What stinks in here?

40:58.417 --> 41:03.463
I bet it's my TV dinner.

41:05.882 --> 41:08.510
We've got a real problem here.

41:08.677 --> 41:12.681
- I'm not the one in trouble.
- We'll see about that.

41:12.889 --> 41:17.602
Don't turn this on me. It's not
my fault your grades have fallen.

41:17.769 --> 41:21.523
You're wrong. The shit you're
telling me keeps me up all night.

41:21.690 --> 41:26.361
I fall asleep during class.

41:28.071 --> 41:32.534
I need a fucking pencil.
Do you have one?

41:32.701 --> 41:37.998
- What will your parents do?
- They won't ever see the letter.

41:38.165 --> 41:44.004
This isn't just a little slip-up.
My parents will freak.

41:44.171 --> 41:50.343
They'll want to know exactly
what happened. Do you get it?

41:53.054 --> 41:56.558
- I think so.
- You'd better be sure.

41:56.767 --> 42:01.104
It'll be your ass that winds up
in jail, not mine. I need a pencil.

42:01.271 --> 42:05.275
A sharp one, please. Thank you.

42:05.442 --> 42:10.405
Does this Edward French
know your parents socially?

42:10.614 --> 42:13.617
They wouldn't mix with that geek.

42:13.784 --> 42:18.080
And professionally,
has he ever spoken to them?

42:18.288 --> 42:22.584
No, I've never needed it till now.

42:25.962 --> 42:31.510
- Don't mess up that carbon paper.
- What would you know about it?

42:31.676 --> 42:36.223
I was forging documents
before your parents were born.

42:54.658 --> 42:57.619
- Todd.
- Do you know what this is about?

42:57.786 --> 43:01.456
I'm sorry, I don't.

43:08.463 --> 43:12.717
That's my son,
he's always chewing gum.

43:12.884 --> 43:16.096
He means the world to me.

43:16.263 --> 43:20.934
- Todd, have a seat.
- Hello there.

43:22.602 --> 43:25.981
It's okay, sit down.

43:29.192 --> 43:34.823
We've talked about what's been going
on. Do you want to talk about it?

43:37.492 --> 43:42.038
- Not really.
- Don't be embarrassed.

43:42.205 --> 43:46.585
It's not your fault. We both want
to help you get back on track.

43:46.752 --> 43:49.921
Both of you?

43:50.088 --> 43:56.678
I must admit that the situation
in Richard's home is appalling.

43:56.887 --> 44:01.683
I always believed a man should
take responsibility for his family.

44:01.892 --> 44:07.814
When you came to me in tears
and asked me to intervene, -

44:07.981 --> 44:12.778
- then I realised this was not
a matter to be trifled with.

44:12.944 --> 44:17.199
That's why I arranged this meeting.

44:17.365 --> 44:19.576
We appreciate your concern.

44:20.744 --> 44:27.167
Todd, I've seen your record,
and every grade is way down.

44:27.417 --> 44:33.298
Even your strongest subject,
history, is down from A to C-.

44:33.465 --> 44:37.469
Trigonometry down to a D.

44:37.636 --> 44:43.517
Did you know you were on your way
to finishing first in your class?

44:45.602 --> 44:49.189
Your grandfather and I
have been talking.

44:49.356 --> 44:55.695
