01:26:42.786 --> 01:26:47.416
- You stop that kind of talk.
- How about this kind of talk?

01:26:54.631 --> 01:26:58.301
That's just a warning.

01:26:58.468 --> 01:27:02.556
If you crave for Florence's food,
that's a weird craving.

01:27:02.723 --> 01:27:08.812
- Jenny's the one who's pregnant.
- They had something to tell us.

01:27:09.020 --> 01:27:12.607
We 're going
to be grandparents again.

01:27:12.816 --> 01:27:16.862
Ijust can't wait
to tell everybody.

01:29:15.981 --> 01:29:19.735
What's wrong?

01:29:45.761 --> 01:29:48.388
Wake up.

01:29:51.808 --> 01:29:57.856
- Are you talking to me?
- Yes, I'm speaking to you.

01:30:19.669 --> 01:30:23.090
Mr. Kramer
is recuperating elsewhere.

01:30:23.298 --> 01:30:26.802
- Are you awake now, Dussander?
- Yes.

01:30:26.968 --> 01:30:32.099
But you seem to have confused me
with someone else.

01:30:32.307 --> 01:30:38.313
My name is Denker.
You have the wrong room.

01:30:38.522 --> 01:30:42.192
My name is Weiskopf,
and you are Kurt Dussander.

01:30:42.401 --> 01:30:48.740
I know no one by that name.
Should I call the nurse?

01:30:50.575 --> 01:30:57.165
Benjamin Kramer was imprisoned
for 1 0 months at Patin.

01:30:57.332 --> 01:31:01.002
You were responsible for the death
of his wife and daughters.

01:31:01.211 --> 01:31:05.674
My name is Arthur Denker.
I am an American.

01:31:05.882 --> 01:31:11.430
Don't bother. Your papers won't
stand up to serious examination.

01:31:12.514 --> 01:31:15.350
We have all we need here.

01:31:15.559 --> 01:31:19.688
I'm Dan Richler, FBl.
This is Detective Getty, LAPD.

01:31:19.855 --> 01:31:24.818
You know who I work for. When you're
strong enough you will be moved.

01:31:25.068 --> 01:31:28.447
Until then, this entire ward
will be under guard.

01:31:28.613 --> 01:31:33.285
You can expect to be in Jerusalem
by the end of the summer.

01:31:51.344 --> 01:31:56.391
- Where do you want us to sit?
- Anywhere but the front row.

01:31:56.558 --> 01:31:59.728
There's Carla.

01:31:59.936 --> 01:32:03.440
- Hi, Chelsea.
- Congratulations.

01:32:12.741 --> 01:32:16.411
- Hey, Todd.
- Mr. French.

01:32:16.578 --> 01:32:20.707
You did it. I knew you could.
I'm so proud of you.

01:32:20.874 --> 01:32:25.754
- These must be your parents.
- Dick Bowden.

01:32:25.921 --> 01:32:30.801
Your son really pulled one off.
You must be very proud.

01:32:30.967 --> 01:32:37.933
- Are you a teacher of Todd's?
- I'm his guidance counsellor.

01:32:38.100 --> 01:32:41.686
I was looking forward
to seeing your grandfather.

01:32:41.895 --> 01:32:46.066
It's a long trip from Charlotte.
He's been in a wheelchair for years.

01:32:46.233 --> 01:32:50.445
They don't get out much.
Usually Thanksgiving.

01:32:53.073 --> 01:32:57.077
I'm sorry ... I don't understand.

01:32:59.496 --> 01:33:03.834
- That's your cue.
- That's my cue.

01:33:04.000 --> 01:33:07.504
Nice to meet you.

01:33:10.841 --> 01:33:14.594
I don't feel so well.
Let's leave early.

01:33:14.845 --> 01:33:19.599
- Are you okay?
- It's probably nerves.

01:33:19.766 --> 01:33:21.810
Let's see how it goes.

01:33:25.897 --> 01:33:31.820
All great achievements
arose from dissatisfaction.

01:33:33.238 --> 01:33:37.409
It is the desire to do better,
to dig deeper, -

01:33:37.576 --> 01:33:41.705
- that propels a civilisation
to greatness.

01:33:41.872 --> 01:33:45.542
All of us
have heard the story of lkaros.

01:33:45.709 --> 01:33:49.212
The young boy who took
the wings his father built for him.

01:33:49.421 --> 01:33:53.175
Wings that were meant to carry him
over the ocean to freedom.

01:33:53.341 --> 01:33:59.347
He used them instead
for a joyride.

01:34:08.440 --> 01:34:13.487
For a brief moment lkaros felt
what it was like to live as a god.

01:34:14.362 --> 01:34:18.533
To touch the sun.
To soar above the common man.

01:34:19.659 --> 01:34:23.038
And for doing so
he paid the ultimate price.

01:34:24.748 --> 01:34:28.168
Come down to the cellar,
you won't believe this.

01:34:28.377 --> 01:34:31.880
Like lkaros,
we too have been given gifts:

01:34:32.047 --> 01:34:37.386
Knowledge, education, experience.

01:34:38.678 --> 01:34:42.432
And with these gifts
comes the responsibility of choice.

01:34:42.641 --> 01:34:46.228
We alone decide how our talents
are bestowed upon the world.

01:34:46.436 --> 01:34:52.067
This is our destiny, and we hold it
in the palm of our hands.

01:35:48.790 --> 01:35:55.672
An investigation by police, FBl,
and the Department of Justice, -

01:35:55.839 --> 01:36:01.344
- has uncovered a body
in the house of Arthur Denker, -

01:36:01.511 --> 01:36:06.475
- the man believed
to be a Nazi war criminal.

01:36:06.683 --> 01:36:09.519
Cause of death has been withheld.

01:36:09.686 --> 01:36:15.650
Identification of the body
is pending further investigation.

01:36:15.817 --> 01:36:20.363
The apprehension of Dussander
brings to a close a manhunt -

01:36:20.530 --> 01:36:24.367
- that has been underway
for 40 years in three continents.

01:36:35.670 --> 01:36:39.007
I'll be taking care of you now.

01:36:40.675 --> 01:36:44.346
Try to relax.

01:36:45.222 --> 01:36:49.684
I'm Dan Richler of the FBl,
and this is Dr. Weiskopf.

01:36:49.851 --> 01:36:53.438
I'd like to hear about
your involvement with Dussander.

01:36:53.605 --> 01:36:58.485
Actually, to you Arthur Denker.
How did you know him?

01:36:58.693 --> 01:37:03.115
- Do you feel up to this.
- Yeah, I'll be fine.

01:37:10.205 --> 01:37:12.249
Here's the thing ...

01:37:12.416 --> 01:37:18.380
You said Denker had a heart attack
while you were reading him a letter.

01:37:18.547 --> 01:37:22.300
- Was it in English or German?
- German.

01:37:23.844 --> 01:37:26.596
- You speak German?
- No.

01:37:26.763 --> 01:37:33.353
- You had no idea what it said?
- No, but he seemed to understand.

01:37:39.401 --> 01:37:43.405
What we can't seem to figure out
is the letter, Todd.

01:37:43.572 --> 01:37:49.244
- Do you know where it is?
- I guess it's still on the table.

01:37:49.453 --> 01:37:56.043
Then it should still be there.
Did you see it, Mr. Bowden?

01:37:56.251 --> 01:38:00.589
No, I wasn't looking for a letter.
I was concerned about Todd.

01:38:00.756 --> 01:38:05.135
- Maybe somebody took it.
- Why would somebody steal a letter?

01:38:05.302 --> 01:38:11.266
Unless they wanted to protect him.
Another fugitive.

01:38:11.475 --> 01:38:14.978
I know all this sounds
like Robert Ludlum, -

01:38:15.187 --> 01:38:22.444
- but while Dussander was in the
hospital someone swiped the letter.

01:38:22.652 --> 01:38:27.407
- That doesn't make sense.
- Why not?

01:38:28.325 --> 01:38:33.205
If he had an old Nazi buddy in town,
why didn't he read the letter?

01:38:33.413 --> 01:38:36.416
Maybe he's crippled or blind.

01:38:36.583 --> 01:38:41.713
Guys that are blind don't normally
go scooting out to steal letters.

01:38:43.131 --> 01:38:47.636
Did he ever talk about his past?

01:38:50.472 --> 01:38:53.183
No.

01:38:53.350 --> 01:38:58.814
- What kind of doctor are you?
- I'm a school teacher.

01:38:59.815 --> 01:39:03.402
Dr. Weiskopf is a professor
at the Judaic lnstitute in Munich.

01:39:03.610 --> 01:39:09.366
He assists the lsraeli Government
in certain matters.

01:39:45.485 --> 01:39:49.531
Hey, buddy, are you okay?

01:39:49.698 --> 01:39:53.535
- Yeah, I'm fine.
- Are you sure?

01:39:56.621 --> 01:40:01.960
I just can't believe it.
Even after what those guys told me.

01:40:02.127 --> 01:40:06.173
Your mother and I
feel like we let you down.

01:40:06.339 --> 01:40:13.221
- It's not your fault.
- We're going to talk to a lawyer.

01:40:13.388 --> 01:40:18.852
It's nothing to worry about.
I just don't trust these cops.

01:40:19.019 --> 01:40:21.646
I think that's a good idea.

01:40:21.813 --> 01:40:26.318
Your old man's on top of this.
I'll take care of this.

01:40:29.446 --> 01:40:31.990
Dad ...

01:40:32.199 --> 01:40:37.788
- I never knew anything about this.
- I never thought you did.

01:40:37.954 --> 01:40:42.918
- I know.
- See you later.

01:40:48.799 --> 01:40:54.262
- Will you talk to the boy again?
- I don't think so.

01:40:54.471 --> 01:40:58.558
Somehow he didn't even ...

01:40:58.725 --> 01:41:04.314
When you were a boy,
what did you do for fun?

01:41:05.524 --> 01:41:08.527
I went to the movies.

01:41:08.693 --> 01:41:14.491
- What did you do?
- I used to chase girls.

01:41:16.827 --> 01:41:20.330
And now I chase old men.

01:41:49.025 --> 01:41:56.241
This is the hospital administrator
and his chief of staff.

01:41:57.367 --> 01:42:01.038
- Do we have a plan?
- They've arranged an exit for us.

01:42:13.216 --> 01:42:17.721
Mr. French, what are you doing here?

01:42:27.230 --> 01:42:31.860
- Are your parents home?
- No. What is it about?

01:42:32.069 --> 01:42:36.698
- That's between me and them.
- Why isn't it between you and me?

01:42:38.742 --> 01:42:42.329
Do you want to tell me
what happened?

01:43:43.390 --> 01:43:47.310
Turn him on his left side.

01:43:50.147 --> 01:43:54.776
- I wouldn't know where to begin.
- You have to tell me something.

01:43:56.653 --> 01:44:01.616
I can tell you it would be better
if we both forget about it.

01:44:01.825 --> 01:44:05.412
I'm sorry, I can't do that.

01:44:14.629 --> 01:44:19.176
Tell your parents
I'll be back to see them later.

01:44:19.342 --> 01:44:23.180
Mr. French ...

01:44:23.388 --> 01:44:27.434
I thought we had a deal here.
"The world will open up for you."

01:44:27.601 --> 01:44:32.647
- You want me to forget about this?
- I want to get on with my life.

01:44:32.856 --> 01:44:39.654
It was a mistake to come here.
I'll do this over the phone.

01:44:43.992 --> 01:44:49.498
Hey, Ed? Can I call you Ed, now
that I'm out of your fucking school?

01:44:54.711 --> 01:44:59.591
Does it ever work?
Or am I the first one?

01:44:59.800 --> 01:45:03.845
If I'm the first, I'm flattered,
but I don't believe that.

01:45:04.012 --> 01:45:10.185
Not after you fixing my grades.
Giving me your home phone number.

01:45:10.352 --> 01:45:14.439
You've got some balls!

01:45:14.606 --> 01:45:18.527
Is this why your wife left you?

01:45:24.533 --> 01:45:28.537
You must really have wanted
to shake my hand or something else.

01:45:28.704 --> 01:45:32.541
Are you going to tell people
I did something to you?

01:45:32.749 --> 01:45:35.877
I'll drag you down with me.

01:45:36.044 --> 01:45:41.466
- I'm better at this than you are.
- I'm trying to help you.

01:45:41.633 --> 01:45:45.053
- I won't just do nothing.
- You're going to fucking have to!

01:45:49.599 --> 01:45:56.732
The things I'm going to say,
they'll never go away.

01:45:58.692 --> 01:46:04.364
Think of your job.
Think of your son.

01:46:21.298 --> 01:46:26.845
What's the story here, Ed?
Do we have a deal?

01:46:33.435 --> 01:46:37.272
You can't do this, Todd.

01:46:37.481 --> 01:46:40.233
You have no idea what I can do.

